    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 996.2 Carrera is powered by the 3.6L M96 horizontally opposed six-cylinder, featuring VarioCam Plus for optimized lift and timing. The power is managed by a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, providing crisp engagement and a direct mechanical connection. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity, with the multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts offering precise turn-in and minimal lateral deflection. Crucially, this example has undergone an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a Rear Main Seal (RMS) replacement, addressing common failure points of the M96 architecture. The braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers with ventilated rotors, showing consistent bite and no thermal warping. While the Arctic Silver finish displays minor road-derived patina, the car remains a mechanically stout platform for the enthusiast prioritizing analog feedback and flat-six performance.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 25
    },
    {
